Quobie
Discuss your favorite book quotes (Genius for books).

1. A library/database of great literature quotes
2. Search quotes by content, book, author, or book genre
3. Add quotes to the database that haven't been added yet
4. Each quote has its own page, complete with discussions, claps, and sharing on social media
5. Add quotes to your personal collection/board


quote {
  id: number,
  title: !string,
  page: number,
  line: number,
  author: !string,
  genre: string, (romance, scifi, prose, non-fiction, poetry, etc.)
  type: string, (inspiration, motivation, prose, poetry, etc.)
  content: !string,
  user: id,
  claps: number,
  flags: number,
  comments: array,
}

user {
  id: number,
  name: string,
  collections: object,
}

collection {
  id: number,
  userId: number,
  quotes: array,
}

comment {
  id: number,
  content: string,
  author: string,
  claps: number,
  flags: number,
  hidden: boolean,
}


Special Functions
1. Camel-casing titles
2. Duplicate checkers
3. Detecting and deleting external links
5. Sort by (popularity, word match, etc.)


MVP
1. Quotes displaying all meta-data
2. Add quotes
3. Comment
4. Clap
5. Report
6. User accounts

FUTURE FEATURES (in order)
1. Sharing quotes on social media
2. Search and filtering options
3. Save quotes to personal collections
4. Other special functions (see above)
5. Ads and/or affiliate marketing
